    "Moreover, forecasting earthquakes presents a formidable challenge within seismology using ML/DL algorithms, crucial for safeguarding lives and minimizing devastating impacts [37].",
    "For example, the authors in [38] have devised a real-time earthquake forecasting framework tailored for seismogenic regions in southwestern China.",
    "The framework harnesses data from the multicomponent seismic monitoring system known as Acoustic Electromagnetic to Artificial Intelligence (AETA).",
    "This system records data via two sensor types per station: electromagnetic (EM) and geo-acoustic (GA).",
    "The objective is to predict the location and magnitude of earthquakes anticipated in the forthcoming week, utilizing data from the current week."
